ASABA The management of the National Directorate of Employmenton Tuesday began a five-day recruitment and training programme for 50 unemployed youths selected across Delta State as part of the small stock(goat) production training scheme organized by its Rural Employment Promotion Department. In a keynote address at the flag-off and orientation ceremony in Asaba, the state capital, Director-General of the NDE, Mallam Abubakar Nuhu Fikpo, said the scheme aims to train a total of 900 unemployed youths in goat production technology along its value chain using the revolving model of empowerment in 18 selected states of the federation at three states per geo-political Zone. According to Fikpo, who was represented by Mrs. Enebeli Roseline, Acting Zonal Director, South-South Zone, the training is partof thedirectorateâ€™scontributiontochecking therapidgrowth of unemploymentinthecountry, describing the programme as a lifetime opportunity for which the participants should consider themselves privileged to have been selected.